Tombini Says Brazil Slowdown Helping to Contain Inflation

-- B y   F e l i p e   F r i s c h
-- 
2011-09-16T17:32:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/tombini-says-brazil-slowdown-helping-to-contain-inflation.html
Brazil ’s slowing economic growth
and a cooling “at the margin” of its hot labor market are
helping to contain inflation, central bank president Alexandre
Tombini said today at an event in  Sao Paulo .  Brazilian inflation will slow to the 4.5 percent mid-point
of its target range by December 2012, Tombini said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Felipe Frisch in Sao Paulo at 
 ffrisch1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
